<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-34-1218 </DOCNO><TEXT>The suitability of annelids and arthropods as biological indicators forland pollution of the terrestrial ecosystems spruce forest and beechforest was investigated. For this purpose liming and acidification experimentswere carried out. Over ten years dominance and abundance of soil animalswas recorded. It could be shown, that dominance structure of annelidsand arthropods changed significantly.</TEXT></DOC>